# DesignLint — Design Decision Protocol
# Source: DesignLint v1.1 by Ruben Granet
# https://github.com/rubengranet/designlint

## MANDATORY — Before Writing Any UI/UX Code

When asked to build, design, or modify any user interface — web apps, landing pages,
dashboards, iOS screens, Android screens, React Native, or any UI component — you MUST
complete the Design Decision Protocol BEFORE writing code.

### Instructions

1. Read `designlint/SKILL.md` for the full 7-decision protocol.
2. Read `designlint/references/archetypes.md` to pick a design archetype.
3. Read `designlint/references/ux.md` to pick a UX paradigm.
4. Read the relevant platform reference:
   - Web → `designlint/references/web.md`
   - iOS → `designlint/references/ios.md`
   - Android → `designlint/references/compose.md`
   - React Native → `designlint/references/react-native.md`
   - Dashboards → `designlint/references/dashboards.md`

### The 7 Decisions (document in a comment block before code)

1. **Aesthetic Axis** — Pick a mood (Brutalist, Editorial, Luxury, Industrial, etc.)
2. **Typography Contract** — Pick display + body fonts. BANNED: Inter, Roboto, Arial, system-ui, DM Sans, Poppins, Space Grotesk
3. **Color System** — 5 tokens (bg/surface/primary/accent/text). BANNED: purple gradients, default blues, generic dark mode
4. **Spatial Grammar** — Choose: Asymmetric / Breathing room / Dense utility / Editorial bleed / Layered depth / Off-grid
5. **Motion Character** — Choose: Snappy / Elastic / Cinematic / Mechanical / Playful / None
6. **Signature Detail** — One memorable, unexpected UI element
7. **UX Paradigm** — Navigation + Interaction + Data entry + Feedback + Onboarding models

### Anti-Convergence Check (before delivering)

- ✗ No Inter/Roboto as primary font
- ✗ No purple/blue gradient on white
- ✗ No centered-column-only layout
- ✗ No tab bar with 5 generic icons
- ✗ No modal for every action
- ✗ No global success/error toasts
- ✗ No 3-screen onboarding carousel
- ✓ WCAG AA contrast on all text/bg combinations
- ✓ Keyboard focus indicators present

If any check fails, fix it before delivering code.
